commitResults.messageTitle: Implement skeletal version of Duke with echo function Duke renamed to Joker.
commitResults.messageBody: Joker greets the user, echos commands entered by user, and exits when user types bye.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to store text entered by user and list back out for user
Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Creating a task class makes it much easier to mark tasks as done. Another tasklist array also makes it easier to keep track.
Add support for tracking three types of tasks: TodDos, Events, Deadlines Created three classes ToDo, Event, Deadline, which inherit from the Task class.
Add Error Handling for 2 types of errors Error 1: Description of a todo list cannot be empty Error 2: Invalid command/input
Fix some bugs related to bye command
Add support for deleting tasks from the list
Refactor the Code More OOP added.
Refactor the Code Added more OOP.
Add automatically save tasks in hard disk feature Automatically saves when task list changes. Loads data from hard disk when Joker starts up.

Add Support for Joker to read dates and times Store deadline and event dates as a java.time.LocalDate. Accept dates in this format: yyyy-mm-dd (e.g., 2019-10-15) and print in a different format such as MMM dd yyyy (e.g., Oct 15 2019).
